### CarrierRatesQueryV2 Demo - Carrier Lifecycle
### Complete workflow: Query -> Disable -> Delete -> Recreate

@baseUrl = http://localhost:7244/api/v1
@fedExId = "REPLACE_WITH_FEDEX_ID>"

#################################################################
### 1. VERIFY CARRIER IS WORKING (Query Rates)
#################################################################

### Get all carriers first to find FedEx ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/carriers
X-Role: Admin
X-Requested-By: demo.user

### Query rates from all carriers (FedEx should be in results)
POST {{baseUrl}}/rates
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "origin": {
        "postalCode": "90210",
        "countryCode": "US"
    },
    "destination": {
        "postalCode": "10001",
        "countryCode": "US"
    },
    "package": {
        "weight": 10,
        "dimensions": {
            "length": 10,
            "width": 8,
            "height": 6
        }
    }
}

### Query FedEx specifically
POST {{baseUrl}}/rates/carrier/{{fedExId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "carrierId": "{{fedExId}}",
    "origin": {
        "postalCode": "90210",
        "countryCode": "US"
    },
    "destination": {
        "postalCode": "10001",
        "countryCode": "US"
    },
    "package": {
        "weight": 10,
        "dimensions": {
            "length": 10,
            "width": 8,
            "height": 6
        }
    }
}

#################################################################
### 2. DISABLE THE CARRIER
#################################################################

### Submit disable request (as regular user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/carriers/{{fedExId}}/disable-requests
Content-Type: application/json
X-Role: User
X-Requested-By: demo.user

{
    "carrierId": "{{fedExId}}",
    "reason": "Carrier service degradation"
}

### Admin approves the disable request (replace with actual disable request ID)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/disable-requests/<DISABLE_REQUEST_ID>/approve
Content-Type: application/json
X-Role: Admin
X-Requested-By: admin.user

{
    "disableRequestId": "<DISABLE_REQUEST_ID>"
}

### Verify FedEx is now disabled
GET {{baseUrl}}/carriers/{{fedExId}}
X-Role: Admin
X-Requested-By: admin.user

### Query rates again (FedEx should no longer be in results)
POST {{baseUrl}}/rates
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "origin": {
        "postalCode": "90210",
        "countryCode": "US"
    },
    "destination": {
        "postalCode": "10001",
        "countryCode": "US"
    },
    "package": {
        "weight": 10,
        "dimensions": {
            "length": 10,
            "width": 8,
            "height": 6
        }
    }
}

#################################################################
### 3. DELETE THE CARRIER (After Disable)
#################################################################

### Delete FedEx carrier
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/carriers/{{fedExId}}
X-Role: Admin
X-Requested-By: admin.user

### Verify carrier is gone
GET {{baseUrl}}/carriers/{{fedExId}}
X-Role: Admin
X-Requested-By: admin.user

#################################################################
### 4. RE-CREATE THE CARRIER
#################################################################

### Create new FedEx carrier
POST {{baseUrl}}/carriers
Content-Type: application/json
X-Role: Admin
X-Requested-By: admin.user

{
    "name": "FedEx",
    "isEnabled": true
}

### Create FedEx rate endpoint (replace with actual carrier ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/carriers/<NEW_CARRIER_ID>/endpoints
Content-Type: application/json
X-Role: Admin
X-Requested-By: admin.user

{
    "carrierId": "<NEW_CARRIER_ID>",
    "operation": "Rates",
    "endpoint": "http://carrierratesqueryv2-mockfedex/api/fedex/rates"
}

### Verify new carrier is enabled and can receive queries
GET {{baseUrl}}/carriers/<NEW_CARRIER_ID>
X-Role: Admin
X-Requested-By: admin.user

### Query rates (new carrier should appear)
POST {{baseUrl}}/rates
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "origin": {
        "postalCode": "90210",
        "countryCode": "US"
    },
    "destination": {
        "postalCode": "10001",
        "countryCode": "US"
    },
    "package": {
        "weight": 10,
        "dimensions": {
            "length": 10,
            "width": 8,
            "height": 6
        }
    }
}